article.description: — Emmanuel Adedoyin had a career-high 24 points as North Florida easily beat Webber International 103-43 on Saturday.
article.headline: North Florida beats Webber International 103-43
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Emmanuel Adedoyin had a career-high 24 points as North Florida easily beat Webber International 103-43 on Saturday. Adedoyin made 8 of 11 3-pointers. Chaz Lanier had 15 points for North Florida (1-5), which snapped its season-opening five-game losing streak. Carter Hendricksen added 12 points. Jacob Crews had 10 points. Jaylon Myles had 11 points for the Warriors. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Portions of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
